      <div class="app-card status-dev mb-enhanced">
        <div class="app-status-badge dev">In Dev · 3 Patents Filed</div>
        <div class="app-icon">🪞</div>
        <div class="app-name">Mirror Buddy</div>
        <div class="app-tagline">System and Method for Integrated Household Interface Mirror With Resident Inference Model, Multimodal Biometric Monitoring, Autonomic Resonance Intervention, and Voice-Activated Communication and Media Services</div>

        <!-- TRACK 1 -->
        <div class="mb-track-block" style="margin-top:24px;">
          <div class="mb-track-label">TRACK 1 OF 3 — CONSUMER HOUSEHOLD DEVICE</div>
          <div class="mb-track-text">A mirror-form-factor household appliance. Not an app. The glass IS the speaker — an audio transducer mechanically coupled to the mirror substrate produces sound through the reflective surface itself. Operates fully offline. Replaces the shared household phone, family calendar, message board, and photo wall. All household members including young children can use it without a personal device.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="mb-moment-block">
          <span class="mb-moment-label">THE MOMENT</span>
          <span class="mb-moment-text">Music plays. There is no visible speaker. The mirror glass is vibrating. That is the patent claim.</span>
        </div>
        <table class="af-table" style="margin:12px 0 24px;">
          <thead><tr><th>Function</th><th>Implementation</th><th>Cloud Required</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td>Voice commands</td><td>Vosk local ASR — wake word → intent routing</td><td class="val-good">No</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Audio output</td><td>Bone-conduction transducer bonded to glass substrate</td><td class="val-good">No</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Household member ID</td><td>ArcFace embeddings — cosine similarity, local only</td><td class="val-good">No</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Phone / SMS / VoIP</td><td>Shared household terminal — no personal device needed</td><td>Wi-Fi only</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Notes / reminders / photos</td><td>On-device non-volatile storage, voice in/out</td><td class="val-good">No</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Biometric data</td><td>Never transmitted — stored on device only</td><td class="val-good">Never</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <!-- TRACK 2 -->
        <div class="mb-track-block">
          <div class="mb-track-label">TRACK 2 OF 3 — MULTI-MODAL COHERENCE DETECTION AND ADAPTIVE INTERVENTION <span style="font-style:normal; color:#666;">· Patent Filed 2026-04-12</span></div>
          <div class="mb-track-text">System and Method for Multi-Modal Behavioral Coherence Detection and Adaptive Intervention. Detects recursive instability patterns across sensor modalities, computes a unified γ_eff, classifies system state relative to a critical threshold, and selects adaptive interventions. The first patent claim that detects looping behavior across modalities as a unified coherence signal.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="af-table-title" style="margin-top:16px;">Processing Pipeline</div>
        <div class="mb-pipeline">
          <span class="mb-pipe-step">Sensors</span>
          <span class="mb-pipe-arr">→</span>
          <span class="mb-pipe-step">Channel Scores</span>
          <span class="mb-pipe-arr">→</span>
          <span class="mb-pipe-step">Loop Detection</span>
          <span class="mb-pipe-arr">→</span>
          <span class="mb-pipe-step">Fusion</span>
          <span class="mb-pipe-arr">→</span>
          <span class="mb-pipe-step">γ_eff</span>
          <span class="mb-pipe-arr">→</span>
          <span class="mb-pipe-step">C(t)</span>
          <span class="mb-pipe-arr">→</span>
          <span class="mb-pipe-step">Decision</span>
          <span class="mb-pipe-arr">→</span>
          <span class="mb-pipe-step">Response</span>
        </div>

        <table class="af-table" style="margin:12px 0 8px;">
          <thead><tr><th>Equation</th><th>Role</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td class="mono">y_eff = Σ(wᵢ · channelᵢ)</td><td>Weighted coherence fusion across modalities</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="mono">y_eff_adj = y_eff · (1 − k · loop_score)</td><td>Instability adjustment — recursive loops penalize coherence</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="mono">γ_eff = (1 − y_eff_adj) · (2 · γ_c)</td><td>Disorder parameter mapping</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="mono">C(t) = C₀ · exp(−α · γ_eff · t)</td><td>Coherence decay model</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="mono">W = γ_c − γ_eff</td><td>Coherence window — distance from critical threshold</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="mono">V(γ) = C₀ · γ · exp(−α · γ)</td><td>Coherence potential — maximum at γ = 1/α</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <table class="af-table" style="margin:8px 0 24px;">
          <thead><tr><th>State</th><th>Condition</th><th>Intervention</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td><span class="grade ok">FROZEN</span></td><td class="mono">γ_eff &lt; 0.5 · γ_c</td><td>Gentle check — system underactivated</td></tr>
            <tr><td><span class="grade strong">EDGE</span></td><td class="mono">0.5 · γ_c ≤ γ_eff &lt; γ_c</td><td>Engage — optimal coherence zone</td></tr>
            <tr><td><span class="grade liar">COLLAPSED</span></td><td class="mono">γ_eff ≥ γ_c</td><td>Interrupt or silence — threshold breached</td></tr>
